abstract.gco:CharacterString: Statewide coverage of 1930 Places based on population data available from the U.S. Bureau of the Census. Population data is from the Fifteenth Census of the United States (1930 Census of Population)

purpose.gco:CharacterString: To use in GIS systems for historical study and analysis This datasets is made available to interested persons through the University of Arizona's instance of Open Geoportal. It has been provided to assist educators, students, researchers, and policy makers in mapping and/or analysis applications.

credit.gco:CharacterString: Chris Kollen, University of Arizona Library

environmentDescription.gco:CharacterString: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 2; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.2.2.1350

measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: Digitized city boundaries from the following maps: Benson used Benson, 1931 (Sanborn); Bisbee used Bisbee Townsite, 1928; Buckeye, Chandler, Gilbert, Glendale, Mesa, Phoenix, Tempe, Tolleson, and Wickenburg used Maricopa County Annexation File; Clifton used Map of Greenlee County, 1916 (no changes until 1970); Douglas used Douglas, 1929 (Sanborn); Flagstaff used City of Flagstaff, a planning and zoning map for annexation; Globe used City of Globe, 1930; Holbrook used Holbrook, 1927 (Sanborn); Miami used Miami 1948(Sanborn) ; Nogales used Map of Nogales, 1940; Pima used Map of Pima, Territory of Arizona, County of Graham, 1887 (no changes until 1960); Prescott used City of Prescott Annexation History, 2007; Safford used Official Map of the Town of Safford and Additions, April-May 1916 (no changes until 1960); Somerton used City of Somerton Annexation map; Thatcher used Official Map of Thatcher, 1902 (no changes until 1970); Tombstone used Tombstone, Arizona, 1882 (Sanborn; no changes until 1960); Tucson used Tucson Annexation Boundary File; Willcox used Willcox, 1927 (Sanborn); Winslow used Soil Map Arizona, Winslow sheet, 1900 (no changes until 1940), and Yuma used City of Yuma Annexation map. For remaining places, used Geographic Names Information System database for point data. Created a 200 meter buffer around all point data in order to convert into polygons.

value.gco:Record: Accuracy ranges from ~10 meters (Scale 1:1,200) to ~50 meters (Scale 1:63,360).

description.gco:CharacterString: Dataset renamed from 1930_Cities.shp to Arizona_CensusPlaces_1930.shp by Ben Hickson with the University of Arizona Library. Metadata fields corresponding the Open Geoportal Working Group Best Practices Guide (http://opengeoportal.org/working-groups/metadata/) were also updated.
